whole_object: Looks like the couch is truly "sofa"-isticated, lounging around all day without a single cushion in the world!
single_object:
- Sofa: "Why did the sofa break up with the chair? It just couldn't handle the pressure of their relationship!"
- Blanket: "I told my blanket it was too clingy, but it just wrapped itself around me tighter!"
- Floor lamp: "Why did the floor lamp apply for a job? It wanted to brighten up its career!"
- Painting: "I asked the painting how it felt about being hung up all day, and it said it was just 'frame-tastic'!"
- Folding chairs: "Folding chairs are the ultimate multitaskers; they can sit and fold under pressure at the same time!"
- Table: "I told the table it was looking a bit flat, and it replied, 'I’m just trying to keep things level!'"
- Lamp: "Why did the lamp go to school? It wanted to get a little more 'light' on the subject!"
- Cushions: "Cushions are like friends; they always have your back when you need to take a load off!"
